   <title xml:lang="en">IGCH 642</title>
   <noteSet>
      <note>Almost certainly a combined deposit; the  Leg Makedonon and Athens coins taken from circulation c. 130-125 and the Aesillas pieces added to the hd. some forty years later. Inquiries in Macedonia by an Athenian correspondent provided the information that the find originally included about 500 coins, of which one-quarter to onethird were Athenian. The fdc Aesillas coins appearing in numerous European and American sales catalogues from 1961 on undoubtedly came from Siderokastro</note>
